properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 18 at 8:38AM HST until February 20 at 6:00PM HST by NWS Honolulu HI
properties.description:
...WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM HST THURSDAY FOR LANAI
MOLOKAI KAHOOLAWE AND PORTIONS OF BOTH MAUI AND THE BIG ISLAND...

* WHAT...Northeast winds 20 to 35 mph with localized gusts over
50 mph expected.

* WHERE...Lanai

* WHEN...Until 6 PM HST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Winds this strong are capable of downing trees and
causing power outages. Motorists, especially those in high
profile vehicles, are urged to drive with extreme caution.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
properties.instruction:
A Wind Advisory means that sustained winds of at least 30 mph, or
gusts of at least 50 mph, are expected. Motorists should use
extra caution.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM HST THURSDAY
